This paper is about learning manipulation trajectories for assistive robots, which falls under the field of robotics (cs.RO). The proposed method uses a recurrent neural network for learning, which is a common technique in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also mentions the use of simulation environments, which is a common approach in computer vision (cs.CV) and human-computer interaction (cs.HC) research.
